{"type":"message","id":"c24b1295","parentId":"201227c4","timestamp":"2026-03-20T11:37:00.276Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_8cdc96c1-1120-4254-abcf-3b577d996c60","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"give AI assistant access to Gmail Google Workspace API OAuth\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 4625,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ba05bb1e70b64efb\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - googleworkspace/cli: Google Workspace CLI — one command-line tool for Drive, Gmail, Calendar, Sheets, Docs, Chat, Admin, and more. Dynamically built from Google Discovery Service. Includes AI agent skills.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ba05bb1e70b64efb\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/googleworkspace/cli\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c51ec0f529ba24e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\ngws auth setup # one-time: creates a Cloud project, enables APIs, logs you in gws auth login # subsequent scope selection and login · gws auth setup requires the gcloud CLI. If you don&#x27;t have gcloud, use the manual setup below instead. ... Scope limits in testing mode: If your OAuth app is unverified (testing mode), Google limits consent to ~25 scopes. The recommended scope preset includes 85+ scopes and will fail for unverified apps (especially for @gmail.com accounts).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9c51ec0f529ba24e\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"348f4fb2582d8afe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGoogle Workspace AI Assistant: Ultimate Guide\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"348f4fb2582d8afe\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://skywork.ai/blog/ai-bot/google-workspace-ai-assistant-ultimate-guide\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e70186a0fdaa09d4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>Use least‑privilege OAuth scopes</strong>; avoid blanket full‑access scopes if you don’t need them. Keep a human in the loop for sends, event creation, and file changes. Respect quotas and implement backoff for API calls; batch and randomize syncs ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e70186a0fdaa09d4\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 month ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"skywork.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"db5640818ce37ce9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to Give Your AI Agent Full Access to Gmail, Google Docs, Drive & Calendar\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"db5640818ce37ce9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://danieltenner.com/ai-agent-gmail-google-services-setup/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"84556aa07138b43c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHere&#x27;s how we solved it: <strong>two lightweight Python scripts, a skill file that teaches the agent when and how to use them, and standard OAuth2 for auth</strong>. No API wrappers, no SaaS dependencies, no per-seat pricing.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"84556aa07138b43c\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 month ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"danieltenner.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cb8c52b4db3d2b7c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nLet users' Assistants access Google Workspace - Google Workspace Admin Help\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cb8c52b4db3d2b7c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://support.google.com/a/answer/9620347?hl=en\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a4c5d32147d38846\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFor example, the Assistant can ... to Google Workspace for the Google Assistant, <strong>in the Admin console, make sure Search and Assistant and User access to Google Workspace data and services are turned on for your organization</strong>....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a4c5d32147d38846\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"support.google.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4ef251ca9a93771\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGoogle Workspace CLI: Your AI Agents Just Got Access — IQ Source Blog\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4ef251ca9a93771\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.iqsource.ai/en/blog/google-workspace-cli-ai-agents/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"93cf7f6c7fa8a750\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGiving an agent access to the CEO’s Gmail is a governance decision, not an engineering one. The same applies to Drive, Calendar, Admin. Every gws skill requires specific OAuth scopes. “Minimum scope” should be the rule — the agent only sees and touches what it needs.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"93cf7f6c7fa8a750\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"January 15, 2024\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.iqsource.ai\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"give AI assistant access to Gmail Google Workspace API OAuth","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":4625,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ba05bb1e70b64efb\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGitHub - googleworkspace/cli: Google Workspace CLI — one command-line tool for Drive, Gmail, Calendar, Sheets, Docs, Chat, Admin, and more. Dynamically built from Google Discovery Service. Includes AI agent skills.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ba05bb1e70b64efb\">>>","url":"https://github.com/googleworkspace/cli","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9c51ec0f529ba24e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\ngws auth setup # one-time: creates a Cloud project, enables APIs, logs you in gws auth login # subsequent scope selection and login · gws auth setup requires the gcloud CLI. If you don&#x27;t have gcloud, use the manual setup below instead. ... Scope limits in testing mode: If your OAuth app is unverified (testing mode), Google limits consent to ~25 scopes. The recommended scope preset includes 85+ scopes and will fail for unverified apps (especially for @gmail.com accounts).\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9c51ec0f529ba24e\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"348f4fb2582d8afe\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGoogle Workspace AI Assistant: Ultimate Guide\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"348f4fb2582d8afe\">>>","url":"https://skywork.ai/blog/ai-bot/google-workspace-ai-assistant-ultimate-guide","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e70186a0fdaa09d4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>Use least‑privilege OAuth scopes</strong>; avoid blanket full‑access scopes if you don’t need them. Keep a human in the loop for sends, event creation, and file changes. Respect quotas and implement backoff for API calls; batch and randomize syncs ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e70186a0fdaa09d4\">>>","published":"1 month ago","siteName":"skywork.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"db5640818ce37ce9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHow to Give Your AI Agent Full Access to Gmail, Google Docs, Drive & Calendar\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"db5640818ce37ce9\">>>","url":"https://danieltenner.com/ai-agent-gmail-google-services-setup/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"84556aa07138b43c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHere&#x27;s how we solved it: <strong>two lightweight Python scripts, a skill file that teaches the agent when and how to use them, and standard OAuth2 for auth</strong>. No API wrappers, no SaaS dependencies, no per-seat pricing.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"84556aa07138b43c\">>>","published":"1 month ago","siteName":"danieltenner.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cb8c52b4db3d2b7c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nLet users' Assistants access Google Workspace - Google Workspace Admin Help\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cb8c52b4db3d2b7c\">>>","url":"https://support.google.com/a/answer/9620347?hl=en","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a4c5d32147d38846\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFor example, the Assistant can ... to Google Workspace for the Google Assistant, <strong>in the Admin console, make sure Search and Assistant and User access to Google Workspace data and services are turned on for your organization</strong>....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a4c5d32147d38846\">>>","siteName":"support.google.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d4ef251ca9a93771\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGoogle Workspace CLI: Your AI Agents Just Got Access — IQ Source Blog\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d4ef251ca9a93771\">>>","url":"https://www.iqsource.ai/en/blog/google-workspace-cli-ai-agents/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"93cf7f6c7fa8a750\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGiving an agent access to the CEO’s Gmail is a governance decision, not an engineering one. The same applies to Drive, Calendar, Admin. Every gws skill requires specific OAuth scopes. “Minimum scope” should be the rule — the agent only sees and touches what it needs.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"93cf7f6c7fa8a750\">>>","published":"January 15, 2024","siteName":"www.iqsource.ai"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774006620274}}
