{"type":"message","id":"3645ce30","parentId":"5af0b4db","timestamp":"2026-03-20T11:40:07.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Sprint status:** RAG pipeline complete/stable. Task 3 (ingestion) still pending.\n\n**Google Workspace research:** Found some promising options:\n\n1. **Google Workspace CLI (gws)** — Official CLI tool with OAuth, can access Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Docs. Has AI agent skills built-in.\n\n2. **OAuth2 setup** — Standard approach: create Google Cloud project → enable APIs (Gmail, Calendar) → configure OAuth consent screen → generate credentials.\n\n3. **Key constraint:** If your Gmail is @gmail.com (not Google Workspace/organization), OAuth app needs verification from Google for full scope access. Testing mode limited to ~25 scopes.\n\nWant me to dig deeper into any of these?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":40346,"output":239,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774006807728}}
