{"type":"message","id":"badf9996","parentId":"df649bdf","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:27:42.478Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_c70aea9c-2295-4a63-a9b8-d6c8cca17c8c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag_abroadworks/clean_md/outsourcing-customer-care.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":27603,"output":72,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27675,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1774009662478}}
{"type":"message","id":"86420ecf","parentId":"badf9996","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:27:42.492Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_c70aea9c-2295-4a63-a9b8-d6c8cca17c8c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntitle: \"Scaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\"\nsource: https://www.abroadworks.com/blog/outsourcing-customer-care\ncrawled: 2026-03-19\n---\n\n# Scaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\n\nHome\n>\nBlogWorks\n>\nBusiness Strategy\nScaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\nDiscover how customer care outsourcing helps founders reduce attrition, reclaim executive time, and build high-retention teams that increase customer lifetime value and long-term business scalability.\nMarch 16, 2026\nTiny Manyonga\nFree Guide to Hiring Offshore\nLearn how to build a global team, reduce costs, and stay compliant while scaling faster and smarter.\nEnter Your Email Address\nThank you! Please check your inbox.\nOops! Something went wrong while submitting the form.\nKey Takeaways\nCustomer care is a retention engine, not just a support function.\nDomestic support teams often carry hidden costs beyond salary.\nHigh attrition destroys institutional knowledge and customer trust.\nAI alone cannot replace human empathy in customer relationships.\nGlobal customer support professionals deliver stronger stability and retention.\nManaged outsourcing removes the founder from daily operational bottlenecks.\nMost founders are addicted to the hunt for new business, but they forget that retention is the only thing that keeps the lights on long-term. When your shop is small, you can carry the whole customer base in your head and keep everyone happy with raw effort. But the moment you actually succeed and grow, that intimacy breaks and your inbox starts to feel like a war zone. Instead of building the future, you spend your day apologizing to people who used to love your brand. Eventually, you realize you are the primary bottleneck, so you hire \"help\" just to stop yourself from drowning in the noise."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"---\ntitle: \"Scaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\"\nsource: https://www.abroadworks.com/blog/outsourcing-customer-care\ncrawled: 2026-03-19\n---\n\n# Scaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\n\nHome\n>\nBlogWorks\n>\nBusiness Strategy\nScaling High-Retention Teams with Customer Care Outsourcing\nDiscover how customer care outsourcing helps founders reduce attrition, reclaim executive time, and build high-retention teams that increase customer lifetime value and long-term business scalability.\nMarch 16, 2026\nTiny Manyonga\nFree Guide to Hiring Offshore\nLearn how to build a global team, reduce costs, and stay compliant while scaling faster and smarter.\nEnter Your Email Address\nThank you! Please check your inbox.\nOops! Something went wrong while submitting the form.\nKey Takeaways\nCustomer care is a retention engine, not just a support function.\nDomestic support teams often carry hidden costs beyond salary.\nHigh attrition destroys institutional knowledge and customer trust.\nAI alone cannot replace human empathy in customer relationships.\nGlobal customer support professionals deliver stronger stability and retention.\nManaged outsourcing removes the founder from daily operational bottlenecks.\nMost founders are addicted to the hunt for new business, but they forget that retention is the only thing that keeps the lights on long-term. When your shop is small, you can carry the whole customer base in your head and keep everyone happy with raw effort. But the moment you actually succeed and grow, that intimacy breaks and your inbox starts to feel like a war zone. Instead of building the future, you spend your day apologizing to people who used to love your brand. Eventually, you realize you are the primary bottleneck, so you hire \"help\" just to stop yourself from drowning in the noise.","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774009662489}}
