dimavz/whisper-tiny&#x27;, messages=[{&#x27;role&#x27;: &#x27;user&#x27;, &#x27;content&#x27;: &#x27;Hello!&#x27;}], ) print(response.message.content)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"db29451e1a4d124e\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"ollama.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8d75c172035c4aa9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nr/ollama on Reddit: Can I somehow install whisper\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8d75c172035c4aa9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/ollama/comments/1dl412v/can_i_somehow_install_whisper/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"127a451266e49d58\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nLook into Fabric. You can pass results from one model to another ... Open WebUI -&gt; Settings -&gt; Audio -&gt; Speach To Text not what you&#x27;re looking for? I have &quot;Whisper (local)&quot; as an option running the docker image `ollama/ollama:latest`.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"127a451266e49d58\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"June 21, 2024\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.reddit.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b71dbf43a2b256ad\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGitHub - maudoin/ollama-voice: plug whisper audio transcription to a local ollama server and ouput tts audio responses · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b71dbf43a2b256ad\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/maudoin/ollama-voice\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63ab198951d06e2f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>curl https://ollama.ai/install.sh | sh) Download a whisper model and place it in the whisper subfolder</strong> (e.g.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"63ab198951d06e2f\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d75abb091854f6bf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\